igious belonging, this book will appeal to students and scholars of world Christianity, missiology, and the history of Christianity, as well as Southeast Asian studies, secular sociologies, and anthropologists operating within the field of religious studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCambodianszFrancexReligion. 0aCambodianszUnited StatesxReligion. 0aChristian convertszCambodia. 0aChristianityzCambodia. 0aEvangelicalismzCambodia. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aCambodia.  aCambodian Civil War.  aKhmer.  aTheravada Buddhism.  aWorld Christianity.  aconversion.  aethnographic study of indigenous Cambodian evangelicalism.  aethnography.  aevangelicalism.  agenocide.  amultiple religious belonging.  areserve mission.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishz978311131908708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271096667?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271096667423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271096667/original  a978-3-11-131908-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023